sql:
SELECT location, COUNT(*) as total_panels
FROM solar_panels
GROUP BY location;

SELECT panel_id, installation_name, installation_date
FROM solar_panels
WHERE location = 'New York, USA';

SELECT COUNT(panel_id) AS total_installations,
       AVG(expected_lifetime) AS average_lifetime
FROM solar_panels;

SELECT s.location, COUNT(DISTINCT s.panel_id) AS installed_panels_count
FROM solar_panels AS s
GROUP BY s.location;

external_knowledge:
- Active status refers to installations with a non-zero AC current;
- Anomalies are indicated by the presence of non-null inverter errors;
- Performance metrics include the average current and voltage readings, energy and power production, and temperatures;
- Installation performance is summarized by calculating the average values of various measurements over the time span;
- The installation names are sorted alphabetically for easier reference.

sql:
SELECT inverter_id, warranty_expiration_date
FROM inverters
WHERE warranty_expiration_date <= DATE('now', '+3 month');

external_knowledge:
- Silent footsteps of time refers to installation dates;
- Keepers of light symbolize the unique identifiers of each inverter;
- Protective sheath denotes the warranty period of the inverters;
- Golden fields imply the geographic locations associated with California.

sql:
SELECT panel_id, COUNT(inverter_id) AS total_inverters 
FROM inverters
GROUP BY panel_id;
